            "image": {},
            "name": "Health Points",
            "ownership": {
                "dOcXwrUs2VunZl0y": 3,
                "default": -1
            },
            "sort": 2,
            "src": null,
            "system": {},
            "text": {
                "content": "<p>Health Points (HP) are a game statistic representing a creature\u2019s ability to sustain damage. The stronger the creature, the more HP it generally has, signifying the greater difficulty in defeating it.</p><div class=\"book-block book-block-example>A Commoner has 4 HP, a Mastiff has 3 HP, a Cat has 2 HP and a Rat has 1 HP.DC Tip: Most damage a creature takes is nonlethal and just \u201cwears them down\u201d until they get closer and closer to Death\u2019s Door. Lighter hits might graze you, while bigger hits knock you off your feet. The description and roleplay of how damage is taken can change depending on its source and the situation, but Health Points represent how much of a beating you can take before you die.</div><div class=\"book-block book-block-dctip>Most damage a creature takes is nonlethal and just \u201cwears them down\u201d until they get closer and closer to Death\u2019s Door. Lighter hits might graze you, while bigger hits knock you off your feet. The description and roleplay of how damage is taken can change depending on its source and the situation, but Health Points represent how much of a beating you can take before you die.</div>",
                "format": 1
            },
            "title": {
                "level": 1,
                "show": true
            },
            "type": "text",
            "video": {
                "controls": true,
                "volume": 0.5
            }
        },
        {
            "_id": "012e9f5632e1726c",
            "_key": "!journal.pages!8f1ac218e59a6024.012e9f5632e1726c",
            "_stats": {
                "compodiumSource": null,
                "coreVersion": "12.327",
                "createdTime": 1721459260.734043,
                "duplicateSource": null,
                "lastModifiedBy": "dOcXwrUs2VunZl0y",
                "modifiedTime": 1721459260.734043,
                "systemId": "dc20rpg",
                "systemVersion": "0.8.0"
            },
            "flags": {},
            "image": {},
            "name": "Health Points at 1st Level",
            "ownership": {
                "dOcXwrUs2VunZl0y": 3,
                "default": -1
            },
            "sort": 3,
            "src": null,
            "system": {},
            "text": {
                "content": "<p>A PC has a number of Health Points equal to <strong>6</strong> + <strong>Character </strong> <strong>Level</strong> + <strong>Might</strong>. A PC also might gain additional HP from its Ancestry or Class.</p><p><strong>Health Point Formula</strong></p><div class=\"book-block book-block-example>A PC starts with a base of 6 HP. It then adds its Characters Level, which is 1 HP at level 1. Using Standard Array to get your Attributes, the highest starting Might you can have is +3. Before considering any bonuses granted by Ancestry Traits or Class Features the highest starting HP a PC can have is 10 HP (6 + 1 + 3) and the lowest is 5 HP (6 + 1 - 2). Example 2: Certain Ancestries and Classes grant additional HP. For example, the Giantborn Ancestry grants an extra +1 HP, and the Fighter Class grants an extra +1 HP at level 1, for a total HP of 12 HP (10 + 1 + 1).</div><div class=\"book-block book-block-example>Certain Ancestries and Classes grant additional HP. For example, the Giantborn Ancestry grants an extra +1 HP, and the Fighter Class grants an extra +1 HP at level 1, for a total HP of 12 HP (10 + 1 + 1).DC Tip: Make sure you check each of these categories as you level to keep your maximum HP updated. You basically get 1 HP each time you level up + 1 more for each Attribute point you gain in Might. You also might get additional HP from Talents and Features you choose.</div><div class=\"book-block book-block-dctip>Make sure you check each of these categories as you level to keep your maximum HP updated. You basically get 1 HP each time you level up + 1 more for each Attribute point you gain in Might. You also might get additional HP from Talents and Features you choose. 6 + Level + Might + (Possible Class or Ancestry</div><div class=\"book-block book-block-blank>6 + Level + Might + (Possible Class or Ancestry Bonus HP)</div>",
                "format": 1
            },
            "title": {
                "level": 2,
                "show": true
            },
            "type": "text",
            "video": {
                "controls": true,
                "volume": 0.5
            }
        },
        {
            "_id": "e43694cd842fa3b7",
            "_key": "!journal.pages!8f1ac218e59a6024.e43694cd842fa3b7",
            "_stats": {
                "compodiumSource": null,
                "coreVersion": "12.327",
                "createdTime": 1721459260.734043,
                "duplicateSource": null,
                "lastModifiedBy": "dOcXwrUs2VunZl0y",
                "modifiedTime": 1721459260.734043,
                "systemId": "dc20rpg",
                "systemVersion": "0.8.0"
            },
            "flags": {},
            "image": {},
            "name": "Temporary Health Points",
            "ownership": {
                "dOcXwrUs2VunZl0y": 3,
                "default": -1
            },
            "sort": 4,
            "src": null,
            "system": {},
            "text": {
                "content": "<p>Temporary Health Points (Temp HP) are additional Health Points that persist for a limited duration. When you take damage, your Temp HP is reduced first, and then any remaining damage carries over to reduce your HP.</p><p><strong><em>Stacking:</em></strong> Temp HP doesn\u2019t stack. If you gain Temp HP from different effects, you choose which effect to gain Temp HP from, and ignore the Temp HP granted by the other effects.</p><p><strong><em>Duration: </em></strong>Temp HP lasts until you complete a Long Rest, or its reduced to 0 by taking damage. An effect that grants Temp HP may state a shorter duration, such as 1 minute, until you complete a Quick Rest, or a Short Rest. When the duration expires, all Temp HP gained immediately vanish.</p>",
                "format": 1
            },
            "title": {
                "level": 2,
                "show": true
            },
            "type": "text",
            "video": {
                "controls": true,
                "volume": 0.5
            }
        },
        {
            "_id": "f4e83780989a5489",
            "_key": "!journal.pages!8f1ac218e59a6024.f4e83780989a5489",
            "_stats": {
                "compodiumSource": null,
                "coreVersion": "12.327",
                "createdTime": 1721459260.734043,
                "duplicateSource": null,
                "lastModifiedBy": "dOcXwrUs2VunZl0y",
                "modifiedTime": 1721459260.734043,
                "systemId": "dc20rpg",
                "systemVersion": "0.8.0"
            },
            "flags": {},
            "image": {},
            "name": "Health Thresholds",
            "ownership": {
                "dOcXwrUs2VunZl0y": 3,
                "default": -1
            },
            "sort": 5,
            "src": null,
            "system": {},
            "text": {
                "content": "<p>Certain game mechanics affect creatures while their current HP is within certain thresholds.</p><p><strong><em>Bloodied:</em></strong> HP is equal to or lower than 1/2 its HP maximum.</p><p><strong><em>Well-Bloodied:</em></strong> HP is equal to or lower than 1/4 its HP maximum.</p><p><strong><em>Death\u2019s Door:</em></strong> HP is equal to or lower than 0 HP, to a minimum of its Death Threshold</p><p>A creature\u2019s <strong>Death Threshold </strong>is equal to 0 HP minus its Prime Modifier.</p><div class=\"book-block book-block-dctip>If a creature is on Death\u2019s Door, it\u2019s still considered to be Bloodied and Well-Bloodied, because their HP is still below 1/2 their maximum (Bloodied) and 1/4 their maximum (Well-Bloodied).Example: A creature with a maximum HP of 8 is considered Bloodied when its HP is 4 or lower, Well-Bloodied when its HP is 2 or lower, and on Death\u2019s Door when its HP is 0 or lower. If its Prime Modifier is 3, the creature\u2019s Death Threshold is -3 HP. That creature dies if its HP is ever reduced to -3 HP or lower.</div><div class=\"book-block book-block-example>A creature with a maximum HP of 8 is considered Bloodied when its HP is 4 or lower, Well-Bloodied when its HP is 2 or lower, and on Death\u2019s Door when its HP is 0 or lower. If its Prime Modifier is 3, the creature\u2019s Death Threshold is -3 HP. That creature dies if its HP is ever reduced to -3 HP or lower.</div>",
                "format": 1
            },
            "title": {
                "level": 2,
                "show": true
            },
            "type": "text",
            "video": {
                "controls": true,
                "volume": 0.5
            }
        },
        {
            "_id": "c4bbf41424d0903d",
            "_key": "!journal.pages!8f1ac218e59a6024.c4bbf41424d0903d",
            "_stats": {
                "compodiumSource": null,
                "coreVersion": "12.327",
                "createdTime": 1721459260.734043,
                "duplicateSource": null,
                "lastModifiedBy": "dOcXwrUs2VunZl0y",
                "modifiedTime": 1721459260.734043,
                "systemId": "dc20rpg",
                "systemVersion": "0.8.0"
            },
            "flags": {},
            "image": {},
            "name": "Death\u2019s Door",
            "ownership": {
                "dOcXwrUs2VunZl0y": 3,
                "default": -1
            },
            "sort": 6,
            "src": null,
            "system": {},
            "text": {
                "content": "<p>When you are reduced to<strong> 0 HP</strong> or lower, you suffers the following effects:</p><ul><li><strong><em>Exhaustion:</em></strong>You immediately gain<strong>Exhaustion 1</strong>.</li><li><strong><em>Action Point Limit:</em></strong>You can\u2019t spend more than 1 AP until the end of your next turn, until you\u2019re restored to 1 HP or higher.</li><li><strong><em>Concentration:</em></strong>You can\u2019t Concentrate.</li><li><strong><em>Death Save:</em></strong>At the end of each of your turns, you make a Death Save.<strong>Failure:</strong>You take<strong>1</strong>True damage.<strong>Critical</strong> <strong>Failure:</strong>You fall<strong>Unconscious</strong>until you\u2019re restored to 1 HP or higher.<strong>Critical Success:</strong>You\u2019re restored to 1 HP.</li></ul>",
                "format": 1
            },
            "title": {
                "level": 2,
                "show": true
            },
            "type": "text",
            "video": {
                "controls": true,
                "volume": 0.5
            }
        },
        {
            "_id": "8e13002122959882",
            "_key": "!journal.pages!8f1ac218e59a6024.8e13002122959882",
            "_stats": {
                "compodiumSource": null,
                "coreVersion": "12.327",
                "createdTime": 1721459260.734043,
                "duplicateSource": null,
                "lastModifiedBy": "dOcXwrUs2VunZl0y",
                "modifiedTime": 1721459260.734043,
                "systemId": "dc20rpg",
                "systemVersion": "0.8.0"
            },
            "flags": {},
            "image": {},
            "name": "Making Death Saves",
            "ownership": {
                "dOcXwrUs2VunZl0y": 3,
                "default": -1
            },
            "sort": 7,
            "src": null,
            "system": {},
            "text": {
                "content": "<p>When a creature makes a Death Save, it rolls a <strong>d20</strong>. If the result is <strong>10</strong> or higher, it succeeds on its Save. A creature makes Death Saves until it\u2019s restored to <strong>1 HP</strong> or higher, becomes <strong>Stabilized</strong>, or dies.</p>",
                "format": 1
            },
            "title": {
                "level": 3,
                "show": true
            },
            "type": "text",
            "video": {
                "controls": true,
                "volume": 0.5
            }
        },
        {
            "_id": "bda82cfed69de49b",
            "_key": "!journal.pages!8f1ac218e59a6024.bda82cfed69de49b",
            "_stats": {
                "compodiumSource": null,
                "coreVersion": "12.327",
                "createdTime": 1721459260.734043,
                "duplicateSource": null,
                "lastModifiedBy": "dOcXwrUs2VunZl0y",
                "modifiedTime": 1721459260.734043,
                "systemId": "dc20rpg",
                "systemVersion": "0.8.0"
            },
            "flags": {},
            "image": {},
            "name": "Stabilized",
            "ownership": {
                "dOcXwrUs2VunZl0y": 3,
                "default": -1
            },
            "sort": 8,
            "src": null,
            "system": {},
            "text": {
                "content": "<p>A creature that takes the Medicine Action (see the Skill Based Actions section) and succeeds on a <strong>DC 10</strong> Medicine Check can Stabilize a creature on Death\u2019s Door.</p><p>A <strong>Stabilized</strong> creature doesn\u2019t make Death Saves while on Death\u2019s Door. A creature remains Stabilized until it\u2019s restored to <strong>1 HP</strong> or takes damage.</p>",
                "format": 1
            },
            "title": {
                "level": 3,
                "show": true
            },
            "type": "text",
            "video": {
                "controls": true,
                "volume": 0.5
            }
        },
        {
            "_id": "5e4e4c4f85242878",
            "_key": "!journal.pages!8f1ac218e59a6024.5e4e4c4f85242878",
            "_stats": {
                "compodiumSource": null,
                "coreVersion": "12.327",
                "createdTime": 1721459260.734043,
                "duplicateSource": null,
                "lastModifiedBy": "dOcXwrUs2VunZl0y",
                "modifiedTime": 1721459260.734043,
                "systemId": "dc20rpg",
                "systemVersion": "0.8.0"
            },
            "flags": {},
            "image": {},
            "name": "Continuous Damage",
            "ownership": {
                "dOcXwrUs2VunZl0y": 3,
                "default": -1
            },
            "sort": 9,
            "src": null,
            "system": {},
            "text": {
                "content": "<p>Continuous damage (such as <strong>Bleeding</strong> and <strong>Burning</strong>) does not affect your HP while on Death\u2019s Door. You still have these conditions on you, but they don\u2019t deal damage to you unless you\u2019re above 0 HP.</p>",
                "format": 1
            },
            "title": {
                "level": 3,
                "show": true
            },
            "type": "text",
            "video": {
                "controls": true,
                "volume": 0.5
            }
        },
        {
            "_id": "7147f13920a4de42",
            "_key": "!journal.pages!8f1ac218e59a6024.7147f13920a4de42",
            "_stats": {
                "compodiumSource": null,
                "coreVersion": "12.327",
                "createdTime": 1721459260.734043,
                "duplicateSource": null,
                "lastModifiedBy": "dOcXwrUs2VunZl0y",
                "modifiedTime": 1721459260.734043,
                "systemId": "dc20rpg",
                "systemVersion": "0.8.0"
            },
            "flags": {},
            "image": {},
            "name": "Death\u2019s Door After Combat",
            "ownership": {
                "dOcXwrUs2VunZl0y": 3,
                "default": -1
            },
            "sort": 10,
            "src": null,
            "system": {},
            "text": {
                "content": "<p>When Combat ends, any creature on Death\u2019s Door must immediately make a Death Save. They repeat this Death Save every 12 seconds until they become Stabilized, are restored to 1 HP or higher, or die.</p><p><strong>Failure:</strong> The creature takes <strong>1</strong> True damage and falls <strong>Unconscious</strong> until it becomes <strong>Stabilized</strong>. <strong>Success:</strong> The creature becomes Stabilized.</p>",
                "format": 1
            },
            "title": {
                "level": 3,
                "show": true
            },
            "type": "text",
            "video": {
                "controls": true,
                "volume": 0.5
            }
        },
        {
            "_id": "d0f73f2f0a6d95d5",
            "_key": "!journal.pages!8f1ac218e59a6024.d0f73f2f0a6d95d5",
            "_stats": {
                "compodiumSource": null,
                "coreVersion": "12.327",
                "createdTime": 1721459260.734043,
                "duplicateSource": null,
                "lastModifiedBy": "dOcXwrUs2VunZl0y",
                "modifiedTime": 1721459260.734043,
                "systemId": "dc20rpg",
                "systemVersion": "0.8.0"
            },
            "flags": {},
            "image": {},
            "name": "NPC\u2019s on Death\u2019s Door",
            "ownership": {
                "dOcXwrUs2VunZl0y": 3,
                "default": -1
            },
            "sort": 11,
            "src": null,
            "system": {},
            "text": {
                "content": "<p>Monsters and NPCs normally die when they\u2019re reduced to 0 HP, however the Game Master can choose to implement Death\u2019s Door on special enemies. They would drop down to <strong>1 AP </strong>and be on Death\u2019s Door in that same weakened state, leaving a window for them to still talk to the party and get out any \u201clast words\u201d before someone puts them out of their misery.</p>",
                "format": 1
            },
            "title": {
                "level": 3,
                "show": true
            },
            "type": "text",
            "video": {
                "controls": true,
                "volume": 0.5
            }
        },
        {
            "_id": "22a8a83a635b8a09",
            "_key": "!journal.pages!8f1ac218e59a6024.22a8a83a635b8a09",
            "_stats": {
                "compodiumSource": null,
                "coreVersion": "12.327",
                "createdTime": 1721459260.734043,
                "duplicateSource": null,
                "lastModifiedBy": "dOcXwrUs2VunZl0y",
                "modifiedTime": 1721459260.734043,
                "systemId": "dc20rpg",
                "systemVersion": "0.8.0"
            },
            "flags": {},
            "image": {},
            "name": "Death\u2019s Door Sidebar ",
            "ownership": {
                "dOcXwrUs2VunZl0y": 3,
                "default": -1
            },
            "sort": 12,
            "src": null,
            "system": {},
            "text": {
                "content": "<p>When a PC is reduced to 0 HP, they\u2019re on \u201cDeath\u2019s Door\u201d and fighting for their life. This is represented however the player wants to describe this state looking for them. They are NOT unconscious, they\u2019re in a heavily weakened state\u2026 about to die if something isn\u2019t done SOON! They could be prone, crawling on the ground, holding themselves up with their sword, or spitting out blood as they hold on for dear life.</p><p>If your Death's Door Threshold is -3 HP and you take a large enough hit that reduces you to -3 or lower\u2026 you\u2019re instantly dead. If you have 1 HP and take 4 damage\u2026 you die. This means that PCs should avoid getting to low HP while against fearsome enemies at all costs. They should use healing magic, Class Features, spend AP defensively, or use consumables to avoid being at low HP\u2026 like they SHOULD be doing anyway!</p>",
                "format": 1
            },
            "title": {
                "level": 2,
                "show": true
            },
            "type": "text",
